The paper deals with the problem of visually summarizing a large influence graph, which involves techniques from information retrieval, data visualization, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are likely categories, as they cover topics related to network analysis and visualization. Additionally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) are also possible categories, as they involve techniques for processing and presenting large amounts of data in a user-friendly way.
